/*
================================================================================
JOB SCHEDULER ‚Äì COMPLETE THEORY + COMPARISON (ANDROID)
================================================================================

-----------------------------------------
WHAT IS JobScheduler ?
-----------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ JobScheduler is an ANDROID SYSTEM API
‚Ä¢ Introduced in Android 5.0 (API 21)
‚Ä¢ Used to schedule BACKGROUND work intelligently
‚Ä¢ System decides WHEN to run your task based on constraints
‚Ä¢ Optimized for battery, performance, and system health

-----------------------------------------
WHY JobScheduler EXISTS (THE CORE REASON)
-----------------------------------------
Before JobScheduler:
‚Ä¢ Developers ran background work freely
‚Ä¢ Apps drained battery
‚Ä¢ Too many background services
‚Ä¢ Poor user experience

Android‚Äôs solution:
üëâ Centralize background work
üëâ Let SYSTEM decide execution time
üëâ Save battery + CPU + memory

-----------------------------------------
WHY NOT JUST USE Service ?
-----------------------------------------
Service:
‚Ä¢ Runs immediately
‚Ä¢ Runs on main thread by default
‚Ä¢ Developer controls lifecycle
‚Ä¢ Can easily misuse and drain battery

JobScheduler:
‚Ä¢ Runs ONLY when conditions are satisfied
‚Ä¢ System controls execution
‚Ä¢ Automatically paused/resumed
‚Ä¢ Battery-optimized

-----------------------------------------
WHY JobScheduler EVEN IF WE HAVE FLOWS / THREADS ?
-----------------------------------------
Flows / Threads:
‚Ä¢ Only control EXECUTION
‚Ä¢ DO NOT control WHEN system allows execution
‚Ä¢ App-level only

JobScheduler:
‚Ä¢ SYSTEM-level scheduling
‚Ä¢ Survives app kill
‚Ä¢ Survives reboot (optional)
‚Ä¢ Respects device state

üëâ Flows/Threads = HOW to do work
üëâ JobScheduler = WHEN system allows work

-----------------------------------------
WHEN SHOULD YOU USE JobScheduler ?
-----------------------------------------
‚úî Background tasks
‚úî Network dependent work
‚úî Periodic syncing
‚úî Deferred work
‚úî Work that can wait
‚úî Work that must survive app kill

-----------------------------------------
WHEN YOU SHOULD NOT USE JobScheduler ?
-----------------------------------------
‚ùå Immediate UI tasks
‚ùå User-triggered instant actions
‚ùå Very short tasks
‚ùå Foreground-only work

-----------------------------------------
JOB SCHEDULER ‚Äì WORKING PRINCIPLE
-----------------------------------------
1. App creates JobInfo
2. App defines constraints
3. App schedules job
4. Android stores job
5. Android waits for conditions
6. Android starts JobService
7. JobService does work
8. JobService calls jobFinished()

-----------------------------------------
JOB SCHEDULER CORE METHODS
-----------------------------------------
JobInfo.Builder()
‚Üí Define constraints

JobScheduler.schedule()
‚Üí Hand job to Android system

JobService.onStartJob()
‚Üí System starts work

jobFinished()
‚Üí Inform system job is done

onStopJob()
‚Üí System stops job if needed

-----------------------------------------
IMPORTANT CONSTRAINTS YOU CAN SET
-----------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ Network type
‚Ä¢ Charging state
‚Ä¢ Device idle
‚Ä¢ Periodic execution
‚Ä¢ Persistence across reboot

-----------------------------------------
WHY JobScheduler IS BETTER THAN MANUAL THREADS
-----------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ System-managed lifecycle
‚Ä¢ Battery aware
‚Ä¢ App kill safe
‚Ä¢ System throttling support

-----------------------------------------
IS JobScheduler LEGACY ?
-----------------------------------------
‚ùå NO (still valid)
BUT:
‚ö† Direct usage is discouraged in modern apps

RECOMMENDED:
‚úî WorkManager (internally uses JobScheduler)

-----------------------------------------
WHAT IS THE MODERN ALTERNATIVE ?
-----------------------------------------
WorkManager
‚Ä¢ Higher-level API
‚Ä¢ Backward compatible
‚Ä¢ Handles retries
‚Ä¢ Handles constraints
‚Ä¢ Uses JobScheduler internally

-----------------------------------------
COMPARISON TABLE ‚Äì ALL BACKGROUND OPTIONS
-----------------------------------------

| Feature / Tool       | Service | Foreground Service | JobScheduler | AlarmManager | WorkManager |
|----------------------|--------|--------------------|--------------|--------------|-------------|
| Runs immediately     | YES    | YES                | NO           | YES          | NO          |
| Battery optimized    | NO     | NO                 | YES          | NO           | YES         |
| System controlled    | NO     | NO                 | YES          | PARTIAL      | YES         |
| Survives app kill    | NO     | YES                | YES          | YES          | YES         |
| Network constraints  | NO     | NO                 | YES          | NO           | YES         |
| Periodic work        | HARD   | NO                 | YES          | YES          | YES         |
| Recommended today    | ‚ùå     | ‚ö†                  | ‚ö†            | ‚ùå           | ‚úÖ BEST     |

-----------------------------------------
WHEN TO USE WHAT (RULES TO MEMORIZE)
-----------------------------------------

| Use Case                          | Best Choice      |
|----------------------------------|------------------|
| Immediate background task        | Service          |
| User-visible ongoing task        | ForegroundService|
| Time-based exact trigger         | AlarmManager     |
| System-optimized background work | JobScheduler     |
| Guaranteed background work       | WorkManager      |

-----------------------------------------
JOB SCHEDULER vs ALARM MANAGER
-----------------------------------------
AlarmManager:
‚Ä¢ Triggers at EXACT time
‚Ä¢ Not battery friendly
‚Ä¢ No constraints
‚Ä¢ Time-based only

JobScheduler:
‚Ä¢ Constraint-based
‚Ä¢ Battery friendly
‚Ä¢ Not exact timing
‚Ä¢ Smart scheduling

-----------------------------------------
REAL WORLD EXAMPLES
-----------------------------------------
JobScheduler:
‚úî Sync contacts when WiFi available
‚úî Upload logs when charging
‚úî Background cleanup

AlarmManager:
‚úî Alarm clock
‚úî Calendar reminder
‚úî Medicine alert

Service:
‚úî Music playback
‚úî File upload with progress
‚úî Active user task

-----------------------------------------
INTERVIEW ONE-LINERS (VERY IMPORTANT)
-----------------------------------------
‚Ä¢ JobScheduler lets SYSTEM decide when background work should run.
‚Ä¢ It improves battery life by batching background jobs.
‚Ä¢ It is constraint-based, not time-based.
‚Ä¢ WorkManager is the modern recommended alternative.

-----------------------------------------
FINAL SUMMARY (MEMORIZE THIS)
-----------------------------------------
Service = Immediate work
Thread/Flow = Execution mechanism
AlarmManager = Exact time trigger
JobScheduler = Smart system scheduling
WorkManager = Best modern solution

